<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Now that Zend_Controller has an AutoComplete helper with several flavors, form elements should be created to facilitate adding autocompletion at the form level. For example, with a dojo autocompleter, it might:</p>

<ul><li>allow specifying the name of the dojo.data store to use with the element</li>
<li>load the necessary dojo libraries</li>
<li>add the appropriate dojo attributes to the element itself</li>
</ul><p>Similar functionality could be added to the other styles supported with the AutoComplete action helper.</p>

